        "id": 248557,
        "name": "Pickle",
        "username": "pickle_umbrella",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/pickle_umbrella/{size}/48004_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-08-05T09:34:51.606Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal will automatically focus the message box when you first switch to a contact so you can immediately start typing. This is very convenient. However, if you click on something else like an image or your contacts profile, when switching back you must click the message box to begin typing again.</p>\n<p>I think it would be nice to allow you to start typing a message regardless of if youre currently focusing on the chatbox or not. This is one feature from Discord Ive always enjoyed, and Im hoping Signal can get this added too.</p>\n<p>Also, when clicking on notifications it doesnt seem to highlight the message box either. So, when Im on my PC I need to hover down to the message box and click it every time I want to start typing.</p>\n<p>This request is probably a nitpick, but its a small quality of life change that I think would be pretty nice.</p>",
